! <$calc> widget — examples

!! Basic arithmetic & number formatting

| Expression | `out="en-US"` | `out="fr-FR"` |h
| `<$calc>1 + 2 * 3</$calc>` | <$calc>1 + 2 * 3</$calc> | <$calc out="fr-FR">1 + 2 * 3</$calc> |
| `<$calc>1 000 000 / 3</$calc>` (FR thousands space) | <$calc>1 000 000 / 3</$calc> | <$calc out="fr-FR">1 000 000 / 3</$calc> |
| `<$calc>1 234,5 + 1 000,5</$calc>` (FR decimal comma + space thousands) | <$calc>1 234,5 + 1 000,5</$calc> | <$calc out="fr-FR">1 234,5 + 1 000,5</$calc> |
| `<$calc>1,234.56 + 0.44</$calc>` (EN thousands comma + decimal point) | <$calc>1,234.56 + 0.44</$calc> | <$calc out="fr-FR">1,234.56 + 0.44</$calc> |
| `<$calc>2^10</$calc>` | <$calc>2^10</$calc> | <$calc out="fr-FR">2^10</$calc> |
| `<$calc>√144</$calc>` (√ unicode) | <$calc>√144</$calc> | |
| `<$calc>∛27</$calc>` (∛ unicode) | <$calc>∛27</$calc> | |
| `<$calc>2² + 3²</$calc>` (superscripts) | <$calc>2² + 3²</$calc> | |
| `<$calc>½ + ¼</$calc>` (vulgar fractions) | <$calc>½ + ¼</$calc> | |
| `<$calc>π * 2</$calc>` (π unicode) | <$calc>π * 2</$calc> | <$calc out="fr-FR">π * 2</$calc> |
| `<$calc>τ / 2</$calc>` (τ = 2π) | <$calc>τ / 2</$calc> | |

!! Scientific notation

| Expression | Result |h
| `<$calc scientific="always">1234</$calc>` | <$calc scientific="always">1234</$calc> |
| `<$calc scientific="always" out="fr-FR">1234</$calc>` | <$calc scientific="always" out="fr-FR">1234</$calc> |
| `<$calc scientific="auto">0.000001 / 10</$calc>` (auto triggers below 1e-6) | <$calc scientific="auto">0.000001 / 10</$calc> |
| `<$calc scientific="never">0.000001 / 10</$calc>` | <$calc scientific="never">0.000001 / 10</$calc> |

