| `<$calc>(2 + 3i) * (1 - i)</$calc>` | <$calc>(2 + 3i) * (1 - i)</$calc> |
| `<$calc>abs(3 + 4i)</$calc>` (modulus) | <$calc>abs(3 + 4i)</$calc> |

!! Variables via data tiddler

''Prerequisite:'' create a tiddler titled `MyVars` with this content:

```
r: 5
h: 10
density: 2.7
```

Then:

| Expression | Result |h
| `<$calc data="MyVars">π * r^2</$calc>` (circle area) | <$calc data="MyVars">π * r^2</$calc> |
| `<$calc data="MyVars">π * r^2 * h</$calc>` (cylinder volume) | <$calc data="MyVars">π * r^2 * h</$calc> |
| `<$calc data="MyVars">density * π * r^2 * h</$calc>` (mass, kg·cm³ mixed) | <$calc data="MyVars">density * π * r^2 * h</$calc> |

!! Error messages & debouncing

The widget waits 100 ms after the last keystroke before showing an error,
so transient states while typing are never displayed. Examples of errors:

| Expression | Message |h
| `<$calc>sqrt(</$calc>` | <$calc>sqrt(</$calc> |
| `<$calc>1 / 0</$calc>` | <$calc>1 / 0</$calc> |
| `<$calc>sqt(4)</$calc>` | <$calc>sqt(4)</$calc> |
| `<$calc>1 +</$calc>` | <$calc>1 +</$calc> |
| `<$calc silence="yes">not_a_function(1)</$calc>` (silence → blank) | <$calc silence="yes">not_a_function(1)</$calc> |
